# Nesting Blocks

Sometimes, answering one question leads to another question.

Imagine a bouncer at a club:
1. First check: "Are you 18 or older?" (If yes, proceed to next check)
2. Second check: "Do you have an ID?"

In JavaScript, we handle this by placing an `if` statement **inside** another `if` statement! This is called **Nesting**.

```javascript
if (age >= 18) {
  console.log("Old enough.");

  if (hasID === true) {
    console.log("Welcome inside!");
  } else {
    console.log("Go get your ID!");
  }
}
```

