## Keep it Clean

While resting is powerful, it can quickly get out of hand:

```javascript
if (userExists) {
  if (passwordCorrect) {
    if (hasActiveSubscription) {
      if (isNotBanned) {
        console.log("Too much nesting!");
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This is jokingly called the **"Pyramid of Doom"** or **"Callback Hell"**. It makes code incredibly hard to read.

In the next lesson, we'll learn how to use Logical Operators to flatten out pyramids like this! 🚜
